title: The Collected True Blood (IDW|2008-2013|Digital|Empire+Various)
description:
Overview:  <a href=" http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/True_Blood#Marketing" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/True_Blood#Marketing</a>



Contains:   IDW's "True Blood" spin-off comics, compiled per narrative continuity
            and bookended throughout with trade edition covers and single-issue
            cover galleries, plus a couple of bonus pages for volumes marked "TPB".
               
               The Great Revelation (2008)                    (Minutemen-ReZone)
               
               All Together Now     (2010) (Digital-TPB-1280)    (Danger-Empire)
               Tainted Love         (2011) (Digital-TPB-1280)    (Danger-Empire)
               The French Quarter   (2011) (Digital-TPB-1280)    (Danger-Empire)
               
               Where Were You       (2012) (Digital)
               Shake for Me         (2012) (Digital-HR)              (K6-Empire)
               Here We Go Again     (2013) (Digital-1920)            (K6-Empire)
               
            These volumes correspond very closely to the commercial 6-volume trade
            set. In the original format, "All Together Now" was titled "True Blood"
            (2010, 6 issues) and "Where Were You", "Shake for Me", and "Here We Go
            Again" were again serialized as "True Blood" (2012, 14 issues). Note
            that the quality of "Where Were You" isn't quite up to par with the
            rest, but no better original releases are available at this time
